# Testing Conventions

## Current State

This project has no test framework configured yet. Before writing any test, **ask the user** whether tests should be added for the current change.

If tests are to be added, set up **Vitest** with Testing Library — it integrates natively with Next.js and Vite-based toolchains.

## Recommended Setup (Vitest)

```bash
bun add -D vitest @vitejs/plugin-react @testing-library/react @testing-library/user-event @testing-library/jest-dom jsdom
```

`vitest.config.ts`:
```ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react';
import path from 'path';

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
  test: {
    environment: 'jsdom',
    setupFiles: ['./vitest.setup.ts'],
  },
  resolve: {
    alias: { '@': path.resolve(__dirname, '.') },
  },
});
```

`vitest.setup.ts`:
```ts
import '@testing-library/jest-dom';
```

## Unit Test Patterns

- Files: `__tests__/ComponentName.spec.tsx` adjacent to the component
- Import via barrel: `from '../'`
- Test user-visible behavior, not implementation

```tsx
import { render, screen, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event';
import { describe, expect, it } from 'vitest';

import Component from '../';

describe('ComponentName', () => {
  it('renders expected content', () => {
    render(<Component />);
    expect(screen.getByRole('heading')).toHaveTextContent('Title');
  });

  it('responds to interaction', async () => {
    render(<Component />);
    await userEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button'));
    await waitFor(() => {
      expect(screen.getByTestId('result')).toBeInTheDocument();
    });
  });
});
```

## Testing Principles

- Use `waitFor` for async assertions
- Prefer `getByRole` (accessible queries) over `getByTestId`
- Test what the user sees and does — avoid testing internals
- Server Components: test utility functions (`lib/post-utils.ts`, etc.) separately
- Client Components: test via render + interaction

## IMPORTANT

Always confirm with the user whether a test is required before writing one.
